Eskom is expected to hold a briefing on Tuesday on the challenges facing the power utility. This comes after it implemented stage 4 load-shedding after two units tripped. “Regretfully, Eskom has just been forced to implement stage 4 load-shedding at 7.20am following Majuba Unit 5 and Tutuka Unit 4 tripping,” it said on Tuesday. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.